        { "type": "post", "settings": { "category": "MINDSET", "title": "Consistency Over Motivation", "excerpt": "Why showing up every day matters more than feeling ready.", "content": "Motivation is unreliable. It comes and goes with mood, weather, sleep, and what you ate for breakfast.\n\nConsistency is the opposite. It doesn’t care how you feel. It just shows up.\n\nThis is the post-it on the bathroom mirror moment — the boring truth that nobody wants to hear because it’s not exciting. There is no shortcut. There is no perfect routine. There is only doing the work, day after day, even when you don’t feel like it.\n\nThat’s the whole game.", "read_time": "5 min read" } },
